Ranged Legerdemain		KEY:Ranged Legerdemain ~ Monkey Domain	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural.DomainPower																									DESC:You can use the Disable Device and Sleight of Hand skills at a range of 30 feet. Working at a distance increases the normal skill check DC by 5, and you cannot take 10 on this check. Any object to be manipulated must weigh 5 pounds or less. You can only use this ability if you have at least 1 rank in the skill being used.																																																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.35

#Block: Mountain Domain
Foothold				KEY:Foothold ~ Mountain Domain		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural.DomainPower.CheckList																							DESC:As a standard action, you can cause an adjacent stone surface up to 10 feet square to mold itself into ridges and creases. A foothold that is created on a horizontal surface is treated as difficult terrain, and a Medium or smaller creature standing in the area or moving through it takes a -2 penalty on Acrobatics checks and to CMD due to poor footing. A foothold that is created on a vertical surface grants a +10 bonus on Climb checks to climb it. The stone remains altered for 1 hour. You can use this ability %1 times per day.|DomainMountainTimes																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.35	ASPECT:CheckCount|%1|DomainMountainTimes	ASPECT:CheckType|Uses per Day
Thin Air				KEY:Thin Air ~ Mountain Domain		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Aura.Supernatural.DomainPower.CheckList			DEFINE:ThinAirRounds|DomainMountainLVL	DEFINE:ThinAirRange|0										DESC:As a free action, you can surround yourself with a %3-foot aura of supernaturally thin air that draws the breath from creatures adjacent to you. Creatures beginning their turn in the aura are fatigued (Fortitude DC %1 negates). A fatigued creature that begins its turn in the aura must save or suffer from altitude sickness, taking 1 point of ability damage to all ability scores (see page 430 of the Core Rulebook). At 16th level, the aura increases to 10 feet. Creatures that do not breathe are immune to this aura. You can use this ability for %2 rounds per day; the rounds need not be consecutive.|DomainMountainDC|ThinAirRounds|ThinAirRange																																																															BONUS:VAR|ThinAirRange|5	BONUS:VAR|ThinAirRange|5|PREVARGTEQ:DomainMountainLVL,16												SOURCEPAGE:p.35

